          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two equivalent length absorbers consisting  of  light",
                " water   ((H-2)O)   and  heavy  water  ((D-2)O).  The",
                " absorbers consisted  of  stainless  steel  tubes  of",
                " equal  internal  dimensions  (4.2  cm) and different",
                " lengths:  about 199.3 cm (filled with  ((H-2)O)  and",
                " about  200 cm (filled with ((D-2)O).  The lengths of",
                " the absorbers were chosen to satisfy  the  relation:",
                " l-H/l-D  =  V-H/V-D,  where  l  and  V represent the",
                " lengths and molar volumes  of  the  absorbers.  With",
                " this choice the atomic attenuation of the photons in",
                " the two tubes becomes identical,  and the difference",
                " in the transmitted intensities, which varies between",
                " 1.5 and 2.7% over the range of photon energies used,",
                " is  entirely  due  to  the  nuclear  absorption  via",
                " H-2(gamma,n) reaction."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "G"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The absolute photodisintegration  cross  section  was",
                " measured   by   comparing   the  transmitted  photon",
                " intensities after passing the  photon  beam  through",
                " equivalent  length  of  two  absorbers consisting of",
                " light and heavy water."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Standard deviation."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Accurate absolute cross sections  for  the  deuterium",
                " photodisintegration  were experimentally determined,",
                " using an absorption method,  at the photon  energies",
                " in  the  range  from  6 to 11 MeV with uncertainties",
                " generally  less  than  3%.  The  photon  beams  were",
                " produced   by   thermal  neutron  capture,  and  the",
                " absorption through 2 m absorbers of H(2)O and  D(2)O",
                " was measured."
              ]
            }
          ],
